<br>
I rarely get in a situation where a mob that needs to be mezzed is on my pet anymore but it does still happen on the occasional weird pull. <br>
<br>
It almost seems like the /pet back off command has a recast time of sorts.  If I hit pet back off too early, it won't go through again after the mez/stun lands and I miss my window of opportunity.<br>
<br>
So what I've been doing recently is waiting with my finger poised above my pet back off hotkey.  The SECOND I see the message that the stun/mez spell landed, I pound away.  This seems to work well.<br>
<br>
I've seen people say they put a bunch of pet back offs in a hotkey and I've toyed with other macro ideas, but waiting for the spell message is what has worked best for me.  Anyone have a better method they would like to share? <p><font face="Times new roman" size="4"><b><font 
