<br>
In places like seb, chanter stuns the mob, i hit /pet back off right away.  I notice that if the mobs do come out of the stun before the mez go off, they will hop on a PC instead of the pet.<br>
<br>
In places like velks, chanter stuns the mob, I usually don't hit /pet back off right away because if the spider comes out of stun before mez goes off it will hit your pet if it's the closest.  This causes the pet to attack again and most likely breaking the mez.  <br>
<br>
I used to hit /pet back off before mobs die all the time when seb was the main place to level.  It prevents pet from breaking any mezzes, controls them better, and if a snare is missed the pet wouldn't go run off.  But now I've become old and lazy.  I don't do that anymore.  Besides, it generates more spam than needed <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   And now that everybody is leveling in velks it really doesn't matter because velks takes absolutely no skill.  &quot;huh my pet ran off? it's no problem he'll either solo the spider or we get some free pulls from lower spider. YAY!&quot;  <br>
<br>
So, point is, different zones has different ways you should control your pet.  And that velkator the sorceror is building an army of lvl 60 zerglings.<br>
<br>
